1
00:00:05,129 --> 00:00:06,865
(Previously)
Can I take over your shop?

2
00:00:06,949 --> 00:00:07,960
I'm not selling.

3
00:00:08,223 --> 00:00:11,149
But if you see the shop and are okay with
a partnership…

4
00:00:11,412 --> 00:00:13,310
I'll draft a contract and send it for you
to sign.

5
00:00:18,666 --> 00:00:19,466
Deal.

6
00:00:33,333 --> 00:00:34,133
Hia

7
00:00:36,200 --> 00:00:38,100
What exactly are we?

8
00:00:39,166 --> 00:00:42,900
I'm whatever you want me to be.

9
00:00:44,100 --> 00:00:46,166
Are we really going to walk around
holding hands like this?

10
00:00:47,966 --> 00:00:49,166
Why should I be embarrassed?

11
00:00:50,866 --> 00:00:52,180
'Cause I'm not cute.

12
00:00:52,355 --> 00:00:53,133
Not petite.

13
00:00:53,800 --> 00:00:55,933
But you're my little one.

14
00:01:00,420 --> 00:01:02,486
Where's the sachet shop?

15
00:01:03,533 --> 00:01:06,466
You're the first person…
who's ever asked where the shop is.

16
00:01:07,533 --> 00:01:09,586
Usually, when I say I'm going to look at
amulets or antiques…

17
00:01:09,669 --> 00:01:12,900
…people either scold me or stop me because
they think I'm weird.

18
00:01:13,866 --> 00:01:15,133
Well, I like this kind of stuff.

19
00:01:20,400 --> 00:01:21,200
Hey.

20
00:01:21,700 --> 00:01:23,266
I've thought of a name for the bar.

21
00:01:24,966 --> 00:01:25,766
ChermChey.

22
00:01:26,366 --> 00:01:27,166
Sure.

23
00:01:27,733 --> 00:01:28,533
It's kinda cute.

24
00:01:29,733 --> 00:01:31,333
I like you even more now.

25
00:01:40,733 --> 00:01:41,533
So cute.

26
00:01:42,566 --> 00:01:44,400
You even keep condoms in a bear pouch.

27
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:11,550
This time, do you want to do it, or should
I?

28
00:02:11,633 --> 00:02:13,018
Do you want to try?

29
00:02:28,156 --> 00:02:28,832
Why so tense?

30
00:02:32,463 --> 00:02:33,608
It's my first time.

31
00:02:44,721 --> 00:02:45,483
That's enough.

32
00:02:48,327 --> 00:02:49,263
Don't force yourself.

33
00:02:51,276 --> 00:02:52,892
You can just do it like usual.

34
00:02:54,892 --> 00:02:55,667
Thanks.

35
00:03:04,235 --> 00:03:05,347
But whenever you feel like it…

36
00:03:09,460 --> 00:03:10,354
…I'm willing to try.

37
00:03:11,404 --> 00:03:11,904
Okay

38
00:03:13,904 --> 00:03:15,466
But this time, I'll do it.

39
00:03:35,371 --> 00:03:36,350
P'In, where are you?
Are you going out tonight?

40
00:03:36,433 --> 00:03:37,371
Are you coming to see me?

41
00:03:37,454 --> 00:03:38,346
I miss you. You just disappeared.

42
00:03:38,429 --> 00:03:40,000
Can we meet up? I'm so lonely.

43
00:03:41,304 --> 00:03:43,523
These are all booty calls.

44
00:03:44,456 --> 00:03:45,256
Hmm?

45
00:03:45,904 --> 00:03:46,870
You bastard, Hia!

46
00:03:47,309 --> 00:03:49,095
Wake up and talk to me right now.

47
00:03:49,690 --> 00:03:50,490
Now!

48
00:03:50,573 --> 00:03:51,060
Yes, dear?

49
00:03:51,323 --> 00:03:52,119
Come here.

50
00:03:52,990 --> 00:03:53,790
What is it?

51
00:03:54,790 --> 00:03:55,590
Yes, love?

52
00:03:58,756 --> 00:04:01,270
Why are you like this? You're such a
scumbag.

53
00:04:01,353 --> 00:04:03,098
A total scumbag.

54
00:04:03,181 --> 00:04:03,598
Look.

55
00:04:03,956 --> 00:04:04,756
What is all this?

56
00:04:12,156 --> 00:04:14,935
Oh, these messages.

57
00:04:17,655 --> 00:04:19,304
They are all the people I talked to
after I broke up with my ex.

58
00:04:20,488 --> 00:04:21,950
Mostly one-night stands and…

59
00:04:22,417 --> 00:04:23,191
That was it.

60
00:04:26,590 --> 00:04:28,290
Here, look.

61
00:04:28,956 --> 00:04:30,123
I never replied to any of them.

62
00:04:31,190 --> 00:04:31,990
See?

63
00:04:34,156 --> 00:04:36,590
I even pinned your chat to the top.

64
00:04:37,756 --> 00:04:38,556
Look.

65
00:04:40,090 --> 00:04:41,290
See? I'm sending you one now.

66
00:04:41,756 --> 00:04:43,790
A 'Good Morning Monday' sticker.

67
00:04:48,090 --> 00:04:48,890
Don't be mad, okay?

68
00:04:50,156 --> 00:04:51,090
I'm not mad.

69
00:04:52,256 --> 00:04:53,056
Then…

70
00:04:53,490 --> 00:04:54,790
Give me a morning kiss.

71
00:05:00,790 --> 00:05:01,590
No.

72
00:05:03,390 --> 00:05:05,123
You have to block them all first.

73
00:05:06,356 --> 00:05:07,156
Okay.

74
00:05:08,156 --> 00:05:09,556
I'll block them right now.

75
00:05:10,356 --> 00:05:11,256
This one, blocked.

76
00:05:14,156 --> 00:05:14,956
I blocked this one

77
00:05:15,323 --> 00:05:15,956
This one also blocked

78
00:05:16,039 --> 00:05:16,956
This one too, blocked blocked.

79
00:05:21,123 --> 00:05:22,256
So you're not mad anymore, right?

80
00:05:23,590 --> 00:05:24,347
No, I'm still mad at you.

81
00:05:25,224 --> 00:05:26,434
I'm craving papaya salad now.

82
00:05:27,556 --> 00:05:30,556
Then let's get some at Tha Nam Non.
It's near my place.

83
00:05:31,156 --> 00:05:32,890
That way, I can pack
my stuff and move in here.

84
00:05:35,356 --> 00:05:36,156
Why would you do that?

85
00:05:36,690 --> 00:05:38,890
If you don't love me,
then don't come…

86
00:05:40,990 --> 00:05:41,790
I do love you.

87
00:05:43,323 --> 00:05:44,297
No, you don't.

88
00:05:44,823 --> 00:05:45,564
I do.

89
00:05:46,090 --> 00:05:47,520
So you'll trust me.

90
00:05:48,222 --> 00:05:50,143
So you'll know that you're the only one I
have.

91
00:05:50,625 --> 00:05:51,448
Besides…

92
00:05:51,790 --> 00:05:53,682
I want to keep an eye on the shop during
the renovation.

93
00:05:54,428 --> 00:05:56,299
I'm too lazy to drive back and forth.

94
00:05:57,966 --> 00:06:00,352
Staying here would be good.

95
00:06:02,890 --> 00:06:04,390
I'm craving Papaya Salad.

96
00:06:08,290 --> 00:06:10,190
I'll pound it extra hard for you.

97
00:06:13,190 --> 00:06:14,056
Who's calling?

98
00:06:14,723 --> 00:06:15,379
My side piece.

99
00:06:15,462 --> 00:06:15,890
Hey!

100
00:06:16,690 --> 00:06:17,490
Just kidding.

101
00:06:17,689 --> 00:06:18,489
It's my friend.

102
00:06:18,856 --> 00:06:19,656
Ai Nai.

103
00:06:22,290 --> 00:06:23,156
You're so slow.

104
00:06:23,290 --> 00:06:24,290
Ow, that hurts.

105
00:06:24,790 --> 00:06:25,590
It hurts.

106
00:07:13,900 --> 00:07:21,400
"ChermChey"
(Episode 3)

107
00:07:36,073 --> 00:07:37,620
Do I have to get used to this weirdness?

108
00:07:38,457 --> 00:07:41,071
I like rugged, classy guys.

109
00:07:41,721 --> 00:07:44,246
But this version of Hia, now that we know
each other…

110
00:07:48,811 --> 00:07:51,205
…is a little outside of my taste.

111
00:07:59,368 --> 00:08:01,143
Oops, I dropped my wallet.

112
00:08:25,690 --> 00:08:26,723
Why are you looking at me like that?

113
00:08:27,556 --> 00:08:28,356
Do you want beef?

114
00:08:28,723 --> 00:08:29,723
Or do you want babies?

115
00:08:32,856 --> 00:08:33,990
I don't want any trouble

116
00:08:34,390 --> 00:08:36,323
and I don’t even have a uterus

117
00:08:38,323 --> 00:08:39,490
Don't feel bad.

118
00:08:40,290 --> 00:08:41,456
If you're with me…

119
00:08:42,156 --> 00:08:43,056
…we don't need to have kids.

120
00:08:43,523 --> 00:08:46,056
Just being Uncle In and Auntie Erng until
we're old is enough.

121
00:08:47,390 --> 00:08:48,856
I want some Spicy Papaya Salad with Rice
Vermicelli.

122
00:08:50,000 --> 00:08:52,800
Hey, I'm trying to talk about marriage
here.

123
00:08:54,856 --> 00:08:57,390
But I want some spicy, zesty Papaya Salad
with Rice Vermicelli

124
00:08:58,904 --> 00:09:01,437
Alright, alright. Go lock the front door.

125
00:09:02,793 --> 00:09:03,593
Clean this up.

126
00:09:18,856 --> 00:09:20,723
Come on, I'm hungry.

127
00:09:24,123 --> 00:09:26,190
I'll get you there in a flash.

128
00:09:26,356 --> 00:09:28,523
But can you stop and buy me a sausage
first?

129
00:09:30,000 --> 00:09:30,800
Of course.

130
00:09:31,748 --> 00:09:32,548
Okay.

131
00:09:34,284 --> 00:09:35,084
Wait.

132
00:09:37,384 --> 00:09:38,850
Isn't your shirt a little low-cut?

133
00:09:45,956 --> 00:09:47,593
Do you want sausage or not?

134
00:09:48,514 --> 00:09:49,260
If you want it, button up.

135
00:09:54,856 --> 00:09:57,411
Please, be a little more modest.

136
00:09:58,464 --> 00:09:59,225
I'm possessive.

137
00:10:08,393 --> 00:10:09,893
Honey, I am serving pure beauty!

138
00:10:11,323 --> 00:10:13,323
Beauty is in the eye of the beholder.

139
00:10:14,915 --> 00:10:15,715
Let's go.

140
00:10:15,937 --> 00:10:16,737
What do you want?

141
00:10:18,137 --> 00:10:18,937
Sausage.

142
00:10:21,271 --> 00:10:22,237
Get whatever I want.

143
00:10:24,190 --> 00:10:25,323
Hia, open the door.

144
00:10:26,671 --> 00:10:28,304
Of course, Young Mistress Erng.

145
00:10:34,871 --> 00:10:35,704
Please have a seat.

146
00:10:41,915 --> 00:10:42,715
Close the door.

147
00:11:03,866 --> 00:11:06,201
Hia.

148
00:11:10,815 --> 00:11:12,415
You don't have to say you love me just
because you're flustered.

149
00:11:12,727 --> 00:11:13,797
Whoa, Hia.

150
00:11:14,367 --> 00:11:15,882
I wasn't going to say I love you.

151
00:11:16,496 --> 00:11:18,473
-I was just going to ask you to buy two cartons of honey
-flavored milk.

152
00:11:19,737 --> 00:11:20,537
Hey!

153
00:11:21,618 --> 00:11:22,243
Roger that!

154
00:11:31,323 --> 00:11:32,390
You deserve a smack for that.

155
00:11:33,723 --> 00:11:34,856
You think you're so cool, huh?

156
00:11:37,456 --> 00:11:38,256
Whoa.

157
00:11:41,590 --> 00:11:43,256
The Ancient Book of Grand Yantras.

158
00:11:44,215 --> 00:11:45,015
Volume One.

159
00:11:51,956 --> 00:11:52,790
You look like you just
walked out of K-drama.

160
00:11:52,890 --> 00:11:53,690
Thanks.

161
00:11:53,890 --> 00:11:55,990
Grandma Kerr, how are you?

162
00:11:56,123 --> 00:11:57,190
It's been so long.

163
00:11:57,456 --> 00:11:58,556
Uncle Aof, hello.

164
00:11:58,790 --> 00:12:00,490
Oh, Nes. Hello.

165
00:12:01,690 --> 00:12:03,156
Erng loves you all!

166
00:12:03,356 --> 00:12:04,156
Hello guys

167
00:12:07,956 --> 00:12:09,256
What's taking so long?

168
00:12:09,339 --> 00:12:14,082
I bet it's either a prayer book or an
amulet magazine.

169
00:12:14,165 --> 00:12:15,356
Famous guru-monks.

170
00:12:33,256 --> 00:12:34,890
What is taking you forever?

171
00:12:35,690 --> 00:12:36,341
What are you doing?

172
00:12:36,424 --> 00:12:36,841
Ow.

173
00:12:36,956 --> 00:12:37,756
I've been waiting so long.

174
00:12:38,856 --> 00:12:39,390
Huh?

175
00:12:39,473 --> 00:12:41,123
Ow, Erng, that hurts.

176
00:12:47,090 --> 00:12:48,456
What book did you buy?

177
00:12:50,723 --> 00:12:52,190
The first volume of the ancient
scriptures.

178
00:12:52,990 --> 00:12:53,890
I knew it.

179
00:13:00,484 --> 00:13:01,712
Erng, dear.

180
00:13:03,203 --> 00:13:06,015
Could you grab me the sachet I bought
yesterday from the car?

181
00:13:06,393 --> 00:13:07,491
Seriously, Hia?

182
00:13:07,842 --> 00:13:09,564
I'm just trying to eat some meatballs
here.

183
00:13:10,178 --> 00:13:11,904
Is that why you need a sachet?

184
00:13:13,706 --> 00:13:14,506
You're nuts.

185
00:13:14,727 --> 00:13:15,793
I was going to change it anyway.

186
00:13:16,050 --> 00:13:17,584
The old one doesn't smell anymore.

187
00:13:27,090 --> 00:13:27,890
Thank you.

188
00:13:35,771 --> 00:13:38,407
Ugh, why can't you open it? Give it to me

189
00:13:41,785 --> 00:13:43,801
You're like the Incredible Hulk.

190
00:13:47,104 --> 00:13:49,537
A minute ago, you still see me
as a cuteie and patootie.

191
00:13:50,716 --> 00:13:52,049
Well, yes, you're my little one

192
00:13:52,390 --> 00:13:53,323
Let's get in the car.

193
00:14:05,790 --> 00:14:07,090
One Spicy papaya salad with Vermicelli

194
00:14:07,790 --> 00:14:08,690
So thoughtful.

195
00:14:11,556 --> 00:14:13,323
So, what goes into a tam pa?

196
00:14:13,656 --> 00:14:14,590
Well, there's teak wood.

197
00:14:14,790 --> 00:14:15,590
Rosewood.

198
00:14:15,656 --> 00:14:16,456
Makha wood.

199
00:14:16,590 --> 00:14:17,690
And a little bit of rudder.

200
00:14:18,156 --> 00:14:19,756
Hey, stop messing with me.

201
00:14:20,090 --> 00:14:20,890
Feet, you say?

202
00:14:21,290 --> 00:14:22,507
You want some fried chicken feet?

203
00:14:22,590 --> 00:14:23,007
Hey!

204
00:14:24,923 --> 00:14:25,890
You want the sticky rice right?

205
00:14:31,556 --> 00:14:32,387
Why so quiet?

206
00:14:32,913 --> 00:14:34,547
Your throat must be dry.

207
00:14:35,249 --> 00:14:38,590
Then I'll order the spicy pork rib soup,
too.

208
00:14:38,756 --> 00:14:39,397
Hey, Hia.

209
00:14:39,967 --> 00:14:41,212
You're messing with me too much.

210
00:14:41,475 --> 00:14:42,543
You're giving me a headache.

211
00:14:43,727 --> 00:14:47,030
How are you so good at turning
my gestures into a food order?

212
00:14:47,336 --> 00:14:50,871
Oh, Intha, Intha. I want to smack you so
hard your bangs will part.

213
00:14:53,923 --> 00:14:55,247
Pork rinds, bear rinds…

214
00:14:56,036 --> 00:14:57,695
Cap… come take a look.

215
00:14:58,528 --> 00:14:59,560
Excuse me.

216
00:15:03,990 --> 00:15:04,790
Hia.

217
00:15:05,756 --> 00:15:07,656
Do you mess with everyone like this?

218
00:15:08,456 --> 00:15:09,256
No.

219
00:15:10,256 --> 00:15:11,790
Only with someone special.

220
00:15:21,590 --> 00:15:23,956
Wow, not a single guy on your feed, huh?

221
00:15:24,156 --> 00:15:25,156
Well, she's cute.

222
00:15:25,556 --> 00:15:29,323
Right, you must have a lot of little sisters.
So many siblings. I'm a sibling too, I guess.

223
00:15:29,756 --> 00:15:30,856
None of them compare to you.

224
00:15:33,190 --> 00:15:33,990
Tell me the truth.

225
00:15:37,890 --> 00:15:39,890
Fine, I like them.

226
00:15:41,723 --> 00:15:43,056
Well, because they're cute.

227
00:15:45,732 --> 00:15:47,672
Your haircut may look like a helmet, Hia.

228
00:15:48,593 --> 00:15:50,655
But it can't protect you from my knockout
punch.

229
00:15:51,523 --> 00:15:52,790
Calm down, Erng.

230
00:15:53,090 --> 00:15:54,490
No violence, okay?

231
00:15:54,990 --> 00:15:55,990
Please sit down.

232
00:16:08,356 --> 00:16:09,923
This is for you, Erng Erng.

233
00:16:11,923 --> 00:16:13,456
Pork sausage only for you.

234
00:16:15,523 --> 00:16:16,323
Mmm.

235
00:16:17,856 --> 00:16:19,323
So, who lives at your house, Hia?

236
00:16:19,790 --> 00:16:21,523
Probably my mom and my younger brother.

237
00:16:22,056 --> 00:16:23,090
Is your mom strict?

238
00:16:24,690 --> 00:16:25,590
She's the kindest.

239
00:16:26,390 --> 00:16:27,063
And…

240
00:16:27,984 --> 00:16:29,356
How many siblings do you have?

241
00:16:29,990 --> 00:16:30,790
Three of us.

242
00:16:31,490 --> 00:16:32,790
Aon, In, and Ong.

243
00:16:34,256 --> 00:16:35,056
All boys.

244
00:16:36,856 --> 00:16:39,190
I'm an only child. My dad is very
protective.

245
00:16:39,890 --> 00:16:40,690
Damn it

246
00:16:41,090 --> 00:16:43,256
And I've already messed with his kid.

247
00:16:43,923 --> 00:16:45,690
Am I going to get shot?

248
00:16:46,856 --> 00:16:48,323
My dad has a shotgun.

249
00:16:48,802 --> 00:16:50,368
And my father will hear about this

250
00:16:51,123 --> 00:16:51,923
Potter.

251
00:16:52,556 --> 00:16:54,990
Then I'll just call a taxi to send you
home from here.

252
00:16:55,090 --> 00:16:56,390
Okay, I'm leaving.

253
00:16:58,056 --> 00:16:58,923
I was just kidding.

254
00:16:59,123 --> 00:17:00,890
Calm down and have a seat, okay?

255
00:17:03,390 --> 00:17:03,975
Little one.

256
00:17:04,545 --> 00:17:05,221
Seriously, though.

257
00:17:05,791 --> 00:17:06,769
Is your dad very protective?

258
00:17:09,971 --> 00:17:11,087
If I were to hit on you…

259
00:17:11,790 --> 00:17:12,731
…what would your dad say?

260
00:17:13,301 --> 00:17:15,383
I'd risk getting shot…

261
00:17:15,778 --> 00:17:17,510
…if it means I can have you by my side.

262
00:17:21,450 --> 00:17:23,859
Are you a human or an angel from heaven?

263
00:17:24,856 --> 00:17:25,656
You're Beautiful.

264
00:17:26,056 --> 00:17:26,856
And so Adorable.

265
00:17:28,256 --> 00:17:30,890
All the praise in the world wouldn't do
you justice.

266
00:17:34,923 --> 00:17:37,456
Sigh. I'm speechless.

267
00:17:39,112 --> 00:17:40,505
This guy is such a player.

268
00:17:40,768 --> 00:17:42,505
In front of others, he acts like a saint.

269
00:17:42,768 --> 00:17:45,643
But with me, he's so flirtatious.

270
00:17:48,090 --> 00:17:49,956
Keep talking trash in your mind and I’m
gonna eat you alive. Ten rounds, babe.

271
00:17:50,271 --> 00:17:51,071
Hmph.

272
00:17:52,523 --> 00:17:53,490
Fine, I'll stop playing around.

273
00:17:54,123 --> 00:17:56,523
For real, how protective is your dad?

274
00:17:57,290 --> 00:17:58,990
So I can prepare myself and get life
insurance.

275
00:17:59,756 --> 00:18:03,156
If my dad were that protective, I wouldn't
be this wild.

276
00:18:04,690 --> 00:18:06,090
Does your dad know you're gay?

277
00:18:06,356 --> 00:18:07,745
He knows. He knows everything.

278
00:18:07,964 --> 00:18:09,824
He knows who I'm dating.

279
00:18:10,263 --> 00:18:12,022
He adored Bom.

280
00:18:22,123 --> 00:18:23,556
I thought you don't eat vegetables, Hia.

281
00:18:26,790 --> 00:18:28,154
It's a bitter feeling.

282
00:18:29,645 --> 00:18:32,185
Believe me, I'm in so much pain that I
can't even tell…

283
00:18:32,755 --> 00:18:33,879
…that these beans stink.

284
00:18:38,390 --> 00:18:41,923
Papaya is a vegetable. I thought you don't
eat vegetables, Hia.

285
00:18:42,256 --> 00:18:42,913
My dear.

286
00:18:43,571 --> 00:18:46,897
Let me tell you, papaya is a fruit.

287
00:18:53,856 --> 00:18:54,890
Are you overthinking this?

288
00:18:56,856 --> 00:18:58,290
About your ex-boyfriend?

289
00:19:00,256 --> 00:19:01,181
I'm sorry.

290
00:19:02,059 --> 00:19:03,488
I won't bring it up again.

291
00:19:04,456 --> 00:19:05,340
I don't know…

292
00:19:05,998 --> 00:19:07,715
…what you went through before you met me.

293
00:19:11,123 --> 00:19:14,556
But once you're mine, you're mine.

294
00:19:18,956 --> 00:19:20,490
You're getting a love bite tonight for
sure.

295
00:20:11,090 --> 00:20:11,970
Mom.

296
00:20:12,365 --> 00:20:13,766
In In is here.

297
00:20:13,985 --> 00:20:15,737
I brought someone with me.

298
00:20:16,290 --> 00:20:18,132
No one's ever brought me home before.

299
00:20:18,921 --> 00:20:20,181
But Hia In…

300
00:20:21,146 --> 00:20:22,875
…is the first person to bring me home.

301
00:20:25,723 --> 00:20:26,990
What do I do now?

302
00:20:27,490 --> 00:20:28,356
This is so awesome.

303
00:20:29,490 --> 00:20:30,290
Erng.

304
00:20:30,556 --> 00:20:31,356
Let's go.

305
00:21:07,656 --> 00:21:08,523
Mom.

306
00:21:09,156 --> 00:21:10,356
In In is here.

307
00:21:13,723 --> 00:21:14,890
I brought someone with me.

308
00:21:15,782 --> 00:21:16,716
Hello, mom

309
00:21:17,090 --> 00:21:18,156
You must be Erng.

310
00:21:18,856 --> 00:21:19,656
Hmm?

311
00:21:19,856 --> 00:21:22,156
You're exactly as In described.

312
00:21:24,590 --> 00:21:25,290
Mom.

313
00:21:25,373 --> 00:21:25,790
Yes?

314
00:21:25,873 --> 00:21:27,156
Did a package arrive for me?

315
00:21:27,323 --> 00:21:28,556
It's over there.

316
00:21:29,656 --> 00:21:31,923
So, have you two eaten yet?

317
00:21:32,456 --> 00:21:34,711
I tried making brownies today.

318
00:21:34,794 --> 00:21:36,056
You should try some.

319
00:21:36,756 --> 00:21:38,123
I'm going to get my package first.

320
00:21:38,556 --> 00:21:40,990
You can let Erng try one first, Mom.

321
00:21:41,290 --> 00:21:43,356
Wow.

322
00:21:43,523 --> 00:21:46,690
Mom, where's Ong?

323
00:21:47,590 --> 00:21:48,856
He's upstairs, of course.

324
00:21:49,723 --> 00:21:51,056
Whenever I bake…

325
00:21:51,390 --> 00:21:52,990
…he always runs up to his room.

326
00:21:53,790 --> 00:21:55,123
That one doesn't like sweets.

327
00:21:55,490 --> 00:21:57,123
No wonder he runs away, Mom.

328
00:21:57,290 --> 00:21:58,090
But…

329
00:21:58,390 --> 00:21:59,256
…Erng…

330
00:21:59,490 --> 00:22:00,290
…will definitely like them.

331
00:22:05,156 --> 00:22:05,956
Yes.

332
00:22:06,656 --> 00:22:09,690
Then you should try my baking today.

333
00:22:20,123 --> 00:22:21,790
Let me help you, Mom

334
00:22:29,190 --> 00:22:29,990
Hmm?

335
00:22:32,923 --> 00:22:34,190
You have big muscles, son.

336
00:22:34,523 --> 00:22:35,690
You look strong.

337
00:22:36,656 --> 00:22:37,456
Thank you.

338
00:22:37,990 --> 00:22:39,756
Oh, it must be ready.

339
00:22:47,123 --> 00:22:49,405
Oh, and is it true, son…

340
00:22:50,019 --> 00:22:51,238
…what In told me?

341
00:22:51,501 --> 00:22:53,578
That you like to dance at ordination
parades?

342
00:22:55,723 --> 00:22:57,744
Uh, yes.

343
00:22:58,358 --> 00:22:59,612
Like this?

344
00:23:01,656 --> 00:23:06,890
Good, son, good. Just like that.
So lively. I love it.

345
00:23:07,523 --> 00:23:11,309
You know, I force Aon, In, and Ong…

346
00:23:11,392 --> 00:23:15,084
…to dance, but they always just stand
there stiffly.

347
00:23:15,167 --> 00:23:16,890
They have no flair at all.

348
00:23:17,890 --> 00:23:18,690
Mom

349
00:23:18,756 --> 00:23:19,256
Yes?

350
00:23:19,339 --> 00:23:22,090
But I'd like to see Hia In dance.

351
00:23:22,723 --> 00:23:24,463
Oh, that's a tough one.

352
00:23:24,546 --> 00:23:25,571
And did you know?

353
00:23:25,654 --> 00:23:27,393
Back in his school days…

354
00:23:27,476 --> 00:23:29,690
…In was the campus heartthrob.

355
00:23:30,290 --> 00:23:30,859
Really?

356
00:23:30,942 --> 00:23:31,359
Mmm

357
00:23:33,328 --> 00:23:34,128
Here.

358
00:23:35,290 --> 00:23:36,156
Try a piece.

359
00:23:36,690 --> 00:23:37,490
Eat while…

360
00:23:37,923 --> 00:23:38,923
…I tell you the story.

361
00:23:39,390 --> 00:23:40,190
Okay.

362
00:23:46,590 --> 00:23:47,390
Is it good?

363
00:23:52,490 --> 00:23:53,856
It's perfectly sweet, Mom

364
00:23:54,290 --> 00:23:56,056
See? Delicious, right?

365
00:23:56,267 --> 00:23:57,633
As for dancing…

366
00:23:57,867 --> 00:24:01,913
In should know that not everyone…

367
00:24:01,996 --> 00:24:03,567
…dances as stiffly as he does.

368
00:24:04,167 --> 00:24:06,900
Mom, what are you telling him now?

369
00:24:09,167 --> 00:24:10,181
Erng.

370
00:24:10,707 --> 00:24:11,904
I saw that.

371
00:24:12,299 --> 00:24:14,324
Were you about to put on
a whole show for my mom?

372
00:24:15,067 --> 00:24:16,242
Take that.

373
00:24:16,549 --> 00:24:20,170
Well, you're the one who
told your mom about me.

374
00:24:21,530 --> 00:24:22,328
Hia.

375
00:24:23,367 --> 00:24:24,100
Want a brownie?

376
00:24:24,183 --> 00:24:26,367
No, thanks. I'd rather put my package away
first.

377
00:24:26,633 --> 00:24:27,733
I have to put my stuff away.

378
00:24:28,433 --> 00:24:29,233
Hey, try some!

379
00:24:29,567 --> 00:24:30,700
I eat them all the time, Mom.

380
00:24:31,100 --> 00:24:32,900
Oh, just try one of my brownies.

381
00:24:33,700 --> 00:24:34,500
Oh.

382
00:24:35,300 --> 00:24:36,100
It's okay.

383
00:24:37,133 --> 00:24:40,890
Um, Mom, you mentioned earlier that
Hia In was the campus heartthrob?

384
00:24:40,973 --> 00:24:44,533
It makes sense that Hia In was the campus
heartthrob, He's handsome.

385
00:24:44,967 --> 00:24:48,036
So, do you think In is handsome, Erng?

386
00:24:48,869 --> 00:24:53,198
Every time he gets a haircut, he never
listens to me. It's so frustrating.

387
00:24:54,267 --> 00:24:55,067
Mom

388
00:24:55,733 --> 00:24:58,243
Hia In is very fashionable.

389
00:24:58,462 --> 00:24:59,861
It's his thing.

390
00:25:00,738 --> 00:25:02,807
It's good that he's true to himself.

391
00:25:03,530 --> 00:25:05,067
Oh, he's just stubborn.

392
00:25:05,150 --> 00:25:05,867
Always.

393
00:25:06,333 --> 00:25:07,133
Is that so?

394
00:25:07,933 --> 00:25:09,467
Hia, you have to block them all first.

395
00:25:10,167 --> 00:25:12,067
Okay, I'll block them right now.

396
00:25:12,467 --> 00:25:13,333
Hia, open the door.

397
00:25:13,667 --> 00:25:15,100
Right away, Young Mistress Erng.

398
00:25:15,467 --> 00:25:17,267
But when Hia In is with Erng…

399
00:25:17,767 --> 00:25:19,833
…he spoils me so bad.

400
00:25:21,867 --> 00:25:22,733
Of course.

401
00:25:24,967 --> 00:25:26,933
Eat up, son. Eat a lot.

402
00:25:33,400 --> 00:25:35,400
You two get along like a house on fire.

403
00:25:37,167 --> 00:25:37,967
So?

404
00:25:38,134 --> 00:25:39,500
Your future sister-in-law.

405
00:25:40,900 --> 00:25:41,700
I don't know.

406
00:25:42,300 --> 00:25:43,002
Move away.

407
00:25:43,528 --> 00:25:44,600
I'm gonna get something to drink.

408
00:25:45,234 --> 00:25:47,034
I don't get involved in couples' drama.

409
00:25:50,434 --> 00:25:51,234
Mom.

410
00:25:51,734 --> 00:25:52,534
Mom.

411
00:25:52,967 --> 00:25:54,534
In threw Ong's cat down.

412
00:25:54,934 --> 00:25:55,734
Ong!

413
00:25:55,767 --> 00:25:56,534
I didn't throw it, Mom.

414
00:25:56,617 --> 00:25:57,488
I didn't throw it.

415
00:25:57,571 --> 00:25:57,988
You did.

416
00:25:58,200 --> 00:25:58,875
I didn't.

417
00:25:58,958 --> 00:25:59,375
You did.

418
00:25:59,500 --> 00:26:00,431
I didn't throw it, Mom.

419
00:26:00,514 --> 00:26:00,931
You did.

420
00:26:00,967 --> 00:26:01,800
Don't lie to me.

421
00:26:01,967 --> 00:26:02,767
Ong is a liar.

422
00:26:03,000 --> 00:26:03,800
I'm not lying.

423
00:26:03,834 --> 00:26:04,934
I really didn't throw it, Mom.

424
00:26:05,100 --> 00:26:05,834
He threw it down.

425
00:26:05,917 --> 00:26:07,534
Oh, stop arguing like children.

426
00:26:08,900 --> 00:26:10,134
I didn't throw it, Mom.

427
00:26:24,860 --> 00:26:26,971
Hey, why are you staring at me like that?

428
00:26:29,000 --> 00:26:31,003
Hello there, handsome.

429
00:26:32,311 --> 00:26:33,776
This one's mine.

430
00:26:35,180 --> 00:26:37,357
I know, but damn, he's got a great aura.

431
00:26:37,971 --> 00:26:39,383
No wonder you like him.

432
00:26:40,304 --> 00:26:42,383
Stay away from him. Go.

433
00:26:42,734 --> 00:26:43,934
What are you two whispering about?

434
00:26:45,800 --> 00:26:47,634
It's nothing, Mom.

435
00:26:47,900 --> 00:26:51,800
Ong just said he wants grilled prawns for
dinner tonight.

436
00:26:52,100 --> 00:26:52,934
That's right, Mom.

437
00:26:54,034 --> 00:26:55,034
Grilled prawns.

438
00:26:56,234 --> 00:26:58,400
Okay, I'll take care of it.

439
00:26:58,934 --> 00:27:01,134
In In, will you stay for dinner tonight?

440
00:27:01,400 --> 00:27:02,767
I'm so happy.

441
00:27:05,727 --> 00:27:08,227
It's been a while since I've eaten

442
00:27:09,231 --> 00:27:09,731
with Mom and Ong.

443
00:27:11,934 --> 00:27:13,034
Don't be a coward.

444
00:27:26,800 --> 00:27:27,934
Just one chili is fine.

445
00:27:45,396 --> 00:27:46,397
What are you guys doing?

446
00:27:50,112 --> 00:27:51,722
Hia, don't come over yet.

447
00:27:51,805 --> 00:27:54,152
Can you change the song for me?

448
00:27:55,292 --> 00:27:56,020
What song?

449
00:27:56,400 --> 00:27:57,634
Anything with a good beat.

450
00:27:59,197 --> 00:28:01,197
Rat-a-tat, rat-a-tat, boom-crash!

451
00:28:02,334 --> 00:28:03,134
How is it?

452
00:28:05,167 --> 00:28:07,800
Dude, move away.

453
00:28:07,883 --> 00:28:08,300
Move a bit farer

454
00:28:12,534 --> 00:28:13,334
In.

455
00:28:13,600 --> 00:28:15,734
Why did you call your brother that just
now?

456
00:28:16,167 --> 00:28:17,100
It's not polite.

457
00:28:17,534 --> 00:28:18,500
That's right, Mom.

458
00:28:20,734 --> 00:28:24,234
Mom, I'll lead the dance team today.

459
00:28:47,500 --> 00:28:49,034
You've got some moves.

460
00:28:49,297 --> 00:28:50,374
Thanks, Mom.

461
00:28:51,814 --> 00:28:53,342
Come on, everyone.

462
00:28:53,425 --> 00:28:55,192
The prawns are ready.

463
00:28:55,275 --> 00:28:56,534
Come and get some prawns.

464
00:28:57,833 --> 00:28:58,967
Hurry.

465
00:28:59,167 --> 00:29:00,167
They're still hot.

466
00:29:00,734 --> 00:29:01,634
Oh, no!

467
00:29:01,900 --> 00:29:02,700
I'm starving.

468
00:29:03,334 --> 00:29:05,167
I'll go first. I'll be back.

469
00:29:06,965 --> 00:29:09,012
- Handing out the weapons.
- It took forever to grill.

470
00:29:09,234 --> 00:29:11,367
Thank you, Mom.

471
00:29:12,167 --> 00:29:13,167
This is as cooked as it gets.

472
00:29:13,367 --> 00:29:14,167
Thank you, Mom.

473
00:29:16,117 --> 00:29:18,117
-Go ahead
-It's so hot!

474
00:29:30,100 --> 00:29:31,700
I'll get some for you, Hia.

475
00:29:36,134 --> 00:29:37,434
Erng, you're so sweet.

476
00:29:37,800 --> 00:29:38,600
Thanks, Mom.

477
00:29:41,700 --> 00:29:45,500
I made the seafood dipping sauce myself,
Hia. Eat up.

478
00:29:52,154 --> 00:29:53,707
Yummyyy

479
00:29:53,790 --> 00:29:55,167
Ong, refill Hia's glass.

480
00:30:12,616 --> 00:30:14,461
Are you sure?

481
00:30:14,544 --> 00:30:16,461
My dear

482
00:30:17,334 --> 00:30:20,000
You said you'd come and ask for my hand

483
00:30:24,400 --> 00:30:25,117
Hey.

484
00:30:25,380 --> 00:30:26,413
Don't tell me…

485
00:30:26,496 --> 00:30:27,967
I'm asking Erng to be my boyfriend.

486
00:30:28,234 --> 00:30:29,534
I thought you said he's my sister-in-law.

487
00:30:30,434 --> 00:30:32,634
Wait, you're not even a couple yet?

488
00:30:32,934 --> 00:30:33,934
So, have you slept together?

489
00:30:41,934 --> 00:30:44,234
Erng won't give in to me, Mom.

490
00:30:51,734 --> 00:30:52,248
Erng.

491
00:30:53,257 --> 00:30:54,256
Will you be my boyfriend?

492
00:31:05,634 --> 00:31:07,900
Let me think about it, Hia.

493
00:31:17,234 --> 00:31:19,367
Even you say no, you'll still get ten
rounds.

494
00:31:19,450 --> 00:31:20,964
I've already racked up dozens!

495
00:31:23,600 --> 00:31:25,200
I'll peel it for you, Erng.

496
00:31:27,300 --> 00:31:32,218
Mom, I'd like to ask you for one more
dance.

497
00:31:33,096 --> 00:31:33,620
May I?

498
00:31:56,167 --> 00:31:57,767
Is being with my family tiring?

499
00:31:58,367 --> 00:31:59,167
It's fun.

500
00:32:20,200 --> 00:32:21,000
Wait.

501
00:32:24,000 --> 00:32:24,800
Sit here for a second.

502
00:32:38,167 --> 00:32:38,967
Hia.

503
00:32:42,534 --> 00:32:43,334
What are you doing?

504
00:32:45,500 --> 00:32:47,034
Are you going to ask me right here?

505
00:33:01,334 --> 00:33:02,534
So cute.

506
00:33:05,800 --> 00:33:06,600
Whose is this?

507
00:33:07,567 --> 00:33:09,000
I kind of want it.

508
00:33:10,567 --> 00:33:11,734
Where did you buy it, Hia?

509
00:33:16,934 --> 00:33:18,334
This notebook is for us.

510
00:33:22,400 --> 00:33:23,234
You bought it for me?

511
00:33:27,134 --> 00:33:27,910
Well…

512
00:33:29,708 --> 00:33:32,249
It's for us to record the stories we
share.

513
00:33:34,567 --> 00:33:35,600
The places we go together.

514
00:33:36,800 --> 00:33:37,900
The meals we eat together.

515
00:33:40,400 --> 00:33:41,367
The time we've been together.

516
00:33:44,300 --> 00:33:45,100
Things like that.

517
00:33:46,434 --> 00:33:48,200
Do you still have the fortune slip?

518
00:33:49,600 --> 00:33:51,134
From when we first met.

519
00:33:54,034 --> 00:33:55,200
I think I still have it.

520
00:33:56,334 --> 00:33:57,700
It should be in my suitcase.

521
00:33:59,034 --> 00:33:59,834
Can you find it for me?

522
00:34:01,234 --> 00:34:02,767
I want to put it in the notebook.

523
00:34:03,500 --> 00:34:05,400
It'll be a record of when we first met.

524
00:34:07,334 --> 00:34:08,134
Okay.

525
00:34:08,634 --> 00:34:09,734
What about yours?

526
00:34:10,400 --> 00:34:11,200
I brought it.

527
00:34:11,767 --> 00:34:12,634
It's in my bag.

528
00:34:13,500 --> 00:34:15,334
I even have the receipt from the shabu
restaurant.

529
00:34:15,900 --> 00:34:17,834
It's a record of the first meal we had
together.

530
00:34:20,700 --> 00:34:21,843
Then tonight…

531
00:34:23,729 --> 00:34:24,452
let's work on the notebook.

532
00:34:25,198 --> 00:34:26,397
I'll also write that…

533
00:34:26,480 --> 00:34:27,944
your mom is lovely…

534
00:34:28,470 --> 00:34:29,725
Ong is annoying…

535
00:34:31,085 --> 00:34:33,422
but he's a good guy.

536
00:34:33,641 --> 00:34:36,194
And that Big brother Araya is super cool.

537
00:34:51,304 --> 00:34:52,338
This notebook…

538
00:34:53,007 --> 00:34:55,058
will be filled with our stories.

539
00:34:55,141 --> 00:34:56,963
And it definitely won't be the last one.

540
00:35:13,234 --> 00:35:14,167
Let's go home.

541
00:35:37,967 --> 00:35:41,100
Seriously, Erng, how many entrances does
your shop have?

542
00:35:50,028 --> 00:35:51,567
Hia, just take the stuff inside.

543
00:35:52,500 --> 00:35:53,300
My back hurts.

544
00:35:53,651 --> 00:35:54,773
I'm not bending over.

545
00:35:56,001 --> 00:35:57,152
Roger that

546
00:35:57,177 --> 00:35:58,759
Whatever my dear Erng commands…

547
00:35:59,655 --> 00:36:01,115
I will gladly do.

548
00:36:01,300 --> 00:36:04,834
Even if my hands are so full that I might trip,
fall and get run over by a car, I'll still do it.

549
00:36:07,534 --> 00:36:08,334
Because of love…

550
00:36:09,700 --> 00:36:10,567
I surrender.

551
00:36:13,600 --> 00:36:16,100
Besides being clingy, you're also a pain
in the ass.

552
00:36:20,600 --> 00:36:22,234
Gosh, this is so heavy, Hia.

553
00:36:22,634 --> 00:36:24,034
Did you bring your whole house?

554
00:36:24,234 --> 00:36:25,434
I'm just a little patootie.

555
00:36:25,934 --> 00:36:27,234
How can I possibly lift this all by
myself?

556
00:36:31,734 --> 00:36:32,800
Just a little patootie?

557
00:36:34,567 --> 00:36:35,800
How little are we talking?

558
00:36:37,034 --> 00:36:39,534
Are your biceps the size of a baby's head
or a coconut?

559
00:36:42,034 --> 00:36:43,134
A 26-inch waist.

560
00:36:43,400 --> 00:36:44,334
A 35-inch chest.

561
00:36:44,634 --> 00:36:45,945
Let me ask you something.

562
00:36:45,970 --> 00:36:47,359
Do you like it? Do you like it?

563
00:36:49,000 --> 00:36:49,800
I love it.

564
00:36:54,200 --> 00:36:56,040
Seeing it makes me want to go for ten…

565
00:36:56,123 --> 00:36:56,600
Oh.

566
00:36:56,827 --> 00:36:59,593
If you're about to say ten rounds, just
stop.

567
00:37:00,234 --> 00:37:02,534
Last night, you passed out on my chest
after only three.

568
00:37:03,167 --> 00:37:03,734
Um…

569
00:37:03,817 --> 00:37:05,434
I feel all sticky. I want to take a
shower.

570
00:37:06,967 --> 00:37:07,767
Erng, You bastard!

571
00:37:11,734 --> 00:37:12,834
Who's this baby face?

572
00:37:13,034 --> 00:37:13,834
It's none of your business.

573
00:37:14,134 --> 00:37:15,034
Is he your new boyfriend?

574
00:37:16,134 --> 00:37:17,567
Why did you come back here?

575
00:37:17,934 --> 00:37:19,500
I saw you changed the shop's name on the
page.

576
00:37:19,934 --> 00:37:20,767
So I thought I'd check it out.

577
00:37:20,967 --> 00:37:22,567
You lock your door now?

578
00:37:24,534 --> 00:37:25,434
Just go back.

579
00:37:26,334 --> 00:37:28,300
Don't make me feel any worse than I
already do.

580
00:37:28,934 --> 00:37:29,900
Let's just stay out of each other's lives.

581
00:37:31,600 --> 00:37:33,000
I've already forgotten you, Bom.

582
00:37:33,934 --> 00:37:36,434
Are you sure you've really forgotten?

583
00:37:37,500 --> 00:37:38,565
I don't believe you.

584
00:37:39,135 --> 00:37:40,634
Have you slept with this baby face yet?

585
00:37:42,300 --> 00:37:43,367
It's none of your business.

586
00:37:48,730 --> 00:37:49,751
Hia.

587
00:37:55,367 --> 00:37:57,200
Don't you touch Erng again.

588
00:37:58,800 --> 00:37:59,600
Get out.

589
00:38:02,034 --> 00:38:03,534
Don't you ever set foot in here again.

590
00:38:11,500 --> 00:38:13,367
Don't ever show your face here again.

591
00:38:15,234 --> 00:38:16,034
Hia.

592
00:38:21,967 --> 00:38:22,934
Let's go inside, Erng.

593
00:38:23,034 --> 00:38:23,900
Are you okay?

594
00:39:57,181 --> 00:39:58,351
Intha &amp; Akara

595
00:40:05,013 --> 00:40:08,110
I used to think… that if I got a new
boyfriend,

596
00:40:08,766 --> 00:40:10,810
I'd have to find someone with a good
personality.

597
00:40:11,685 --> 00:40:13,948
Polite, well-mannered.

598
00:40:14,560 --> 00:40:16,079
But what I got was…

599
00:40:16,998 --> 00:40:19,479
a playboy with an annoying mouth…

600
00:40:20,311 --> 00:40:23,786
who likes to tease me and is a little bit
of a psycho.

601
00:40:26,944 --> 00:40:27,773
As for me…

602
00:40:28,911 --> 00:40:31,178
I never thought someone like Erng would be
this jealous.

603
00:40:31,659 --> 00:40:33,835
Just a notification from a girl popping up
on my phone…

604
00:40:34,303 --> 00:40:35,953
and he's ready to kill me.

605
00:40:36,447 --> 00:40:37,763
But honestly…

606
00:40:38,376 --> 00:40:40,201
when you blocked everyone right in front
of me…

607
00:40:40,595 --> 00:40:42,289
my heart completely melted.

608
00:40:43,295 --> 00:40:44,303
After that,

609
00:40:45,076 --> 00:40:47,076
I took Erng home.

610
00:40:49,658 --> 00:40:52,008
He met my mom and my brother.

611
00:40:55,977 --> 00:40:57,802
And my mom seemed to like him a little too
much.

612
00:41:01,371 --> 00:41:02,977
Well, your mom is so sweet.

613
00:41:05,189 --> 00:41:06,715
And then there were On and Ong.

614
00:41:07,852 --> 00:41:09,583
The younger brother I always mess with.

615
00:41:10,896 --> 00:41:12,263
I wasn't messing with him.

616
00:41:12,346 --> 00:41:14,425
But your brother was staring at me like he
wanted to hit on me.

617
00:41:16,426 --> 00:41:20,295
At first, I thought this was all moving
too fast.

618
00:41:20,994 --> 00:41:22,358
But when we were actually together,

619
00:41:23,146 --> 00:41:26,176
it felt more natural than I expected.

620
00:41:27,863 --> 00:41:30,150
Like we've always been this way.

621
00:41:31,876 --> 00:41:32,649
Same here.

622
00:41:35,362 --> 00:41:36,708
Even though you're weird,

623
00:41:37,556 --> 00:41:40,550
with your amulets and your constant
teasing,

624
00:41:42,153 --> 00:41:44,303
and you say dirty things with a straight
face…

625
00:41:50,047 --> 00:41:51,381
But when I'm with you,

626
00:41:52,081 --> 00:41:54,303
I feel so damn at ease.

627
00:42:03,200 --> 00:42:04,567
(Next Episode)
Go get that wound looked at.

628
00:42:06,500 --> 00:42:08,334
I know this kind of thing will happen
again.

629
00:42:08,967 --> 00:42:11,167
Bom might come back and cause trouble for
us.

630
00:42:16,134 --> 00:42:20,034
Is it selfish if I ask you to be patient
and stay with me?

631
00:42:27,300 --> 00:42:28,834
This might sound over the top,

632
00:42:30,134 --> 00:42:32,000
but I have really strong feelings for you.

633
00:42:35,934 --> 00:42:37,500
You make me feel important.

634
00:42:42,634 --> 00:42:43,534
You make me feel special.

635
00:42:48,734 --> 00:42:50,700
But everything is happening so fast.

636
00:42:51,834 --> 00:42:54,734
Too fast for me to be sure that I won't be
abandoned again.

637
00:43:08,134 --> 00:43:09,800
I can trust you, can't I?

638
00:43:22,367 --> 00:43:24,600
I feel so incredibly lucky that I met you.

639
00:43:32,234 --> 00:43:33,567
If you're having second thoughts,

640
00:43:35,534 --> 00:43:37,000
you're making a big mistake, Erng.

641
00:43:41,434 --> 00:43:42,234
I'm telling you.

642
00:43:44,900 --> 00:43:46,400
Someone as good to you as I am?

643
00:43:47,200 --> 00:43:48,000
You'll never find another.

644
00:43:53,000 --> 00:43:54,834
Get in the car already, princess.

645
00:43:56,167 --> 00:43:58,167
There are no maids here to serve you.
